summary: This FBI 302 form documents an interview attempt with a witness (name redacted) at her residence on May 29, 2008. Agents served her with a grand jury subpoena to testify in the Southern District of Florida regarding Jeffrey Epstein. The witness initially declined to speak without her attorney, Diarmuid White, but later called back seeking more information.

keyFacts: A key witness in the Epstein investigation was subpoenaed to appear before a federal grand jury in West Palm Beach, Florida on June 3, 2008.
The witness initially invoked her right to counsel, providing the business card of her attorney Diarmuid White of the White and White Law Firm in New York.
FBI agents clarified the witness was not a target of investigation but was being interviewed regarding Jeffrey Epstein.
The witness later called FBI SA Johnson on the same day seeking more information about why agents wanted to speak with her.
The document indicates the witness had travel arrangements to consider for the grand jury appearance and mentioned her husband, uncle, and 10-year-old sister.
